docs.description: DAISHIN SECURITIES CO., LTD. is a Korea-based company specialized in the securities and investment banking business. The Company is engaged in the securities dealing, brokerage and underwriting businesses, covering corporate bonds, government bonds, options, foreign exchanges, initial public offerings (IPOs), exchange traded funds, cash management accounts (CMAs), equity linked securities (ELSs), fund wrap accounts , investment strategy consulting and bond analysis services. It also provides Internet banking services. In addition, through its subsidiaries, it engages in the saving bank, asset management, economic research and other businesses.
docs.name: Daishin Securities Co., Ltd (003540)

docs.description: Thai Central Chemical PCL is a Thailand-based company engaged in the manufacture and distribution of chemical fertilizers. The Company operates two plants, located at Phra Samut Chedi district, Samut Prakan province, with total annual capacity of 850,000 metric tons, and at Nakhon Luang district, Phra Nakhon Si Ayutthaya province, with total annual capacity of 350,000 metric tons. The produced chemical fertilizers consist of basic chemical nutrients, such as nitrogen, phosphate, potassium, secondary nutrients, including magnesium, sulphur, and other supplementary nutrients, such as boron. It offers the products under Ox Brand. Through its subsidiaries, it is also involved in industrial chemicals, textile chemicals, plastics, and liquid chemicals businesses. The Company's subsidiaries are MC Agro-Chemicals Co., Ltd., MC Industrial Chemical Co., Ltd., MC Solvents Co., Ltd., MC Plastics Co., Ltd., N.I.M. Co., Ltd. and Central Pacific (Thailand) Corp., Ltd.
docs.name: Thai Central Chemical Public Company Ltd (TCCC)
